////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

ASP Commander

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Thank you for choosing ASP Commander - opensource software
for remote web site administration based on MS Internet Information Services
and Active Server Pages Technology (IIS with ASP and SSI enabled)

INSTALLATION
------------

1. Please unpack sources under a Web-accessible directory, e.g. /aspcommander/
2. Set up the correct owner of the files and give him write permissions
3. Make 'index.asp' file the default ASP index page
4. Check that ASP-pages and SSI-includes are enabled on IIS
5. Replace default 'user' and 'password' in 'config.inc.asp'
6. Use ASP Commander from IE/FF/Chrome/Opera: http://you_site.com/aspcommander/index.asp

Note:
* You can use http://you_site.com/ac/passwd.asp to generate md5(password)
* You can check *.log files to control software access

REQUIREMENTS
------------

- Microsoft Windows NT/2000/XP/2003/Win7/2008/2012
- Microsoft Internet Information Server v5 or above
- ADODB v2.8 (ADODB.Stream) [www.microsoft.com]
- aspSmart (aspSmartUpload.SmartUpload) [http://www.aspSmart.com]
  (if you wish to upload files to server over internet)


FEATURES
--------

1. Drive, directory and file listings
2. Attributes, size, modification date views
3. File creating, viewing, modifying, deletion
4. Directory creating, listing, modifying, deletion
5. File and directory renaming
6. Attributes changing
7. Copy/Paste operations on files and directories
8. Download and Upload files with aspSmartUpload


WHAT's NEXT
-----------

Please visit github page of the project website
for last version and discussion with other users.

http://www.github.com/sundoctor/aspcommander

